Sean Keenihan, Tim Hogan-Doran, Dr Craig Emerson, Daryl Guppy, Ken Smith, Adam Handley, James Young, Laurie Smith, Jingmin Qian, Ben Foskett, Lili Pan | key_people = John Brumby (Chairman) Helen Sawczak(Chief Executive) | website = www.acbc.com.au | staff = 30 - 50 | abbreviation = ACBC }}
{{more citations needed|date=September 2014}}
The '''Australia China Business Council (ACBC)''' was formed in 1973 shortly after the re-establishment of [[Diplomacy|diplomatic ties]] between [[Australia]] and [[China]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.acbc.com.au/overview|title=The Australia China Business Council|website=www.acbc.com.au|access-date=2017-11-21}}</ref>
The Australia China Business Council's primary focus is to promote two way [[investment]] and [[trade]] between Australia and China and is the leading [[business]] organization between the two countries. The Council undertakes various [[thought leader]]ship activities and [[lobbying]] of [[Project stakeholder|stakeholders]].
The presiding President of the Australia China Business Council is [[John Brumby]], the former Premier of Victoria. The current Chief Executive Officer is Helen Sawczak.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.smh.com.au/breaking-news-business/exanz-exec-to-head-china-business-lobby-20160718-4i2uq.html|title=Ex-ANZ exec to head China business lobby|website=The Sydney Morning Herald|access-date=2017-11-21}}</ref> [[Craig Emerson]] former Minister for Trade is President of the Australia China Business Council NSW
The Australia China Business Council, has representative offices in every state and territory in Australia.<ref name=":0" /> In China, the Australia China Business Council works with the Australia Chambers of Commerce to deliver services to its members.
== Events == The Australia China Business Council holds regular events around Australia and in China, including hosting of Chinese delegations to Australia, seminars, networking events and business seminars. ACBC has a number of notable annual events: * Canberra Networking Day <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.canberranetworkingday.com.au|title=Canberra Networking Day|website=ACBC 2017 Canberra Networking Day|access-date=2017-11-21}}</ref> * Chinese New Year Celebrations
