{{More citations needed|date=July 2017}} {{Infobox rugby biography | image = Raffaele Dolfato.jpg | image_size = 200 | caption = Dolfato in a championship match against [[Petrarca Rugby|Petrarca]], 1987 | birthname = | birth_date = {{birth date|df=yes|1962|10|28}} | birth_place = [[Treviso]], [[Italy]] | death_date = {{death date and age|df=y|1997|7|7|1962|10|28}} | death_place = [[San Biagio di Callalta]], [[Treviso Province]] | ru_position = Flanker | ru_amateuryears = | ru_amateurclubs = | ru_clubyears = 1981-1994 | ru_proclubs = [[Benetton Rugby|Benetton Treviso]] | ru_clubcaps = 258 | ru_clubpoints = (?) | ru_nationalyears = 1985-1988 | ru_nationalteam ={{nrut|Italy}} | ru_nationalcaps = 9 | ru_nationalpoints = (0) }}
'''Raffaele Dolfato''' ([[Treviso]], 28 October 1962-[[San Biagio di Callalta]], [[Treviso Province]], 7 July 1997) was an Italian [[rugby union]] player who played as flanker.
==Biography== A dashing flanker, thanks to his not extremely powerful body build type, he debuted in the championship with [[Benetton Rugby|Benetton Treviso]], with which he played for all of his career. He won three Italian Championship titles with Treviso, in 1981,1989, and 1992. He captained the team during the second, and in the third, he joined the try-scoring players hall of fame with a try scored against [[Rugby Rovigo Delta|Rugby Rovigo]].
==International career== He debuted for [[Italy national rugby union team|Italy]] on 3 March 1985 against a [[France national rugby union team|France XV]], and he was among those who were called by the coach [[Marco Bollesan]] for the [[1987 Rugby World Cup]], the first ever Rugby World Cup. He played a total of 9 matches for the Italian team, the last of whose being against [[Soviet Union national rugby union team|USSR]] in 1988.<ref>[http://en.espn.co.uk/statsguru/rugby/player/9852.html International statistics at ESPN Scrum]</ref>
==After career and death== After retiring from the playing career in 1994, Dolfato focused on the clothing company he founded, Dominae. On 7 July 1997 he was killed in a road incident on the Postumia Highway 53, Dolfato crashed head-on with a car, while driving a [[BMW R100]] motorcycle, and died before medical aid arrived.<ref>[http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/action,viewer/Itemid,3/page,0029/articleid,0603_01_1997_0186_0033_8255919/ Rugby, è morto Dolfato]</ref><ref>[http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/1997/luglio/08/tragica_morte_Lello_Dolfato_azzurro_ga_0_9707082473.shtml Tragica morte di Lello Dolfato fu azzurro e tricolore di rugby]</ref>
